rComments: the lectures given by this prof are very poor. no direction is given and random things interrupts what he is talking about. This is followed by him skipping over what he was talking about at the beginning and leaving most students scratching their heads. one of many problems that make his lectures almost impossible to understand and break down.
Worst lecturer I have ever had the misfortune of experiencing; I would've dropped this class if I didn't need it to graduate this year.

Professor Ostapchuk is an excellent professor. He takes interest in his students' success. The course material was fascinating and the lectures and readings were thorough and engaging. The evaluations were fair, and not too difficult if you did the readings. I've never learned so much in any other course. I highly recommend taking NMC 274 or 377.

This prof cannot teach very well. He needs to brush up on his public speaking abilities because his lectures are difficult to comprehend and take notes in. However, if you study your texts well, you can get a really good grade in his courses.

A very understanding man, however, his class can be EXTREMELY boring (other than occasional movies).  I found making notes in his class very difficult b/c I could never understand what he was saying...but if you read all the handouts and know all the definitions of the necessary terms, you are *guarenteed* too do very veryyyyyyy well.
